Multiple_earthquakes_hit_Yunnan_Province
Death toll from China quake rises to 81
2012-09-09 06:18:47 GMT
BEIJING, Sept. 9 (Xinhua) -- A 3.7-magnitude aftershock that occurred in southwest China's Yunnan Province Saturday evening killed one person, the latest victim following multiple earthquakes that hit a mountainous area in the province on Sept. 7.The Ministry of Civil Affairs said Sunday that the quakes have killed 81 people in the city of Zhaotong.The latest victim was a two-year-old child who was fatally injured after being buried under a fallen bounding wall when the aftershock struck.Yunnan has received 59.4 million (9.43 million U.S. dollars) in yuan quake relief funds thus far, the ministry said.
